China Telecom Global and Liquid Telecom have announced a strategic partnership where the companies will collaborate to provide Africa and Asia with network solutions and services. The agreement will enable the companies to serve their enterprise and wholesale customers with extended network coverage across the fastest growing economies in the two regions. China Telecom Global has already established a Point-of-Presence (PoP) at Liquid Telecom’s East Africa Data Centre in Nairobi. It will now establish additional PoPs at Liquid Telecom’s data centre facilities in Johannesburg and Cape Town. China Telecom Global and Liquid Telecom will also continue to explore joint service opportunities under the partnership.